cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with image classification using Fisher Vector classifiers and Deep Neural Networks, which are both commonly used in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the interpretability of these classifiers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses Layer-wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) as a technique to better understand the classifiers, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses potential flaws and biases in data, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
